snippet.title: Bike Tour in Paris - Paris Bike Tour with Bike About Tours
snippet.description:
Paris Bike Tours. If you want to sign up for a bike tour in Paris with Bike About Tours, you can do so here: http://bit.ly/BikeAboutToursJay and be sure to mention me when you reserve to get a sticker ❤️ Bike tours are one of the best outdoor activities in Paris you could do. Links to the photos and more below - Help me make better videos at http://patreon.com/jayswanson and then find me on the internet in all of the usual spots:
http://twitter.com/jayonaboat
http://instagram.com/jayswanson (me) http://bit.ly/ShirtOfTheMonth (merch)
http://bit.ly/JaySwansonBooks (my books)
http://facebook.com/jay.swanson.author

Music by: Dyalla
Camera Four photo scans: https://gum.co/camerafour
Grab a Paris Bike Tour here: http://bit.ly/BikeAboutToursJay I really enjoyed doing bike tours in Paris last year and really highly recommend it if you're up for outdoor activities in Paris. They're really easy, safe, and a fun way to see the city.
Le Ruisseau - Burger Joint: https://goo.gl/maps/HLxX2ZCcERv


My name is Jay Swanson - I'm an American writer living in Paris on an artist visa and hoping to make the city of light my home base - at least for the foreseeable future. I write science-fiction and fantasy, vlog daily, and love pizza a little too much.

FAQ:
How long have you lived in France? On and off for over two years.

What do you miss most about ho- NACHOS

You're always talking about living on some ship. WHAT SHIP? - I made a "Draw My Life" video that explains a lot here: https://youtu.be/-MrvL37jTKM

Where are you from originally? - Pullman, Washington - a small university/agricultural town near Idaho (and yes, the potatoes are amazing).

What do you film with? - I currently film almost exclusively with my Samsung Galaxy S8: http://amzn.to/2lPKSpZ

How do you get those shots where you're walking or running? - A Joby Gorillapod for smartphones, like this: http://amzn.to/2sXNIL3

You drop your phone a lot, how does it survive? - THIS CASE IS AMAZING: http://amzn.to/2hoxgTA (Galaxy S7) - http://amzn.to/2Dt08Bu (Galaxy S8) - http://amzn.to/2FxVliP (iPhone)

What do you edit with? - Adobe Premiere - it's pretty much all I've ever used since high school.

Aren't you ever freaked out by leaving your camera behind to film yourself? - Yep. But not too badly - I tend to be careful when I do.

Why are you living in #Paris? - Because I've always wanted to; I feel at home here: https://youtu.be/4Vivf6MqMxQ

But what are you doing there? - Living it up! https://youtu.be/ZW2RP--DO8Y

Do you speak French? Oui. https://youtu.be/va1QjaHgij8

You talk a lot about the books you're working on, what are they about? - They're sci-fi (and fantasy) and I've got a decent pitch for you here: https://youtu.be/W2bKt4_Tp4E

Do you make money off YouTube? - Ha, no. I wish. It took me over 500 videos to make my first $100 off adsense. I think it will slowly change, but VERY slowly.

I really enjoy your videos, how can I support you? - The easiest and best way to support me is through Patreon, where you can pitch in as little as $1/mo to help me make better videos: http://patreon.com/jayswanson

I don't trust this Patreon thing - what's your PayPal? - Here's a handy link! https://www.paypal.me/jayswanson

I like PayPal in pink! - Here's my ko-fi if that's your thing (and coffee is your game): https://ko-fi.com/jayswanson

But I want to send you something tangible! - I do have a wishlist on Amazon, though it's a bit complicated with the international shipping situation. This is the US one: http://amzn.to/2ykS9Ux

And here's the French one: http://bit.ly/JaysFrenchWishList

Can I come stay with you in Paris? - Have you seen my apartment? It's too small for me as it is! https://youtu.be/6t2qj3rdyX8

OK, but how do I use the Metro when I'm there? - I made a handy video for you: https://youtu.be/T0YS5si8bJs

Well well well...another fun and informative vlog...thanks for that!!!
I'll be visiting in Sept and will definitely schedule a bike tour FIRST THING per your suggestion.

For me, Paris is a city that the more I visit, the more I learn and the more I don't know and must return! Paris is like crack...it's addictive!

Full disclosure- I've never done crack.😳

I wish I could have been there with you to join in your group it would have been so much more fun that way! comments.textDisplay: I hope you do not take this the wrong way but I have watched your vlog for a while and you talked about how you did not like the vlogs that made peoples lives seem perfect however I find it unusual that you are doing a vlog about Paris and have totally neglected to mention a knife attack that took place in the heart of the city less than a week ago.  Obviously if you are worried about them yanking your visa if you say anything I can understand that but simply acknowledging it and saying that the city is doing well or banded together I do not think would jeopardize your status.  If someone were to watch this vlog three or four years from now they would have no idea the attack ever occurred sort of like doing a vlog about New York and never mentioning 911.  I also find it kind of disrespectful to the person or people that were killed that the rest of you guys in Paris totally ignored their loss while you drink coffee and take pictures of space invaders.  I will conclude with this and then I am going to unsubscribe. It seems to me the more money you make on patron and the better off you are doing the more shallow your vlog is becoming. I first came to your vlog because I kind of shared in your struggles of trying to transition and make a new life for myself however as I watch your vlogs now all it ever seems about is coffee, latte’s, field trip‘s and merchandise.  I hope you find what you are looking for in life but I will leave you with a saying from the Bible  “A double minded man is unstable in all his ways”.

replies.textDisplay: Thanks David and 300 for chiming in, I appreciate you taking the time. Solo, if I were to take time out of my day for every tragedy that occurred in the world, or even just in Paris, I would never be able to share my own life. That's all this vlog is intended to be in the end. There is a lot more that I could say about this but I don't know that it would be helpful so I'll just leave it at that - I hope you find what you're looking for as well!

replies.textDisplay: Jay's vlogs give us a glimpse of his life in Paris, and he comes to us as a writer who shares his daily routine and adventures with us. Why would he be obligated to bring us the news as well?   The news media do a good job of that.  I can't help but notice that you seem a tad resentful of his recent good fortune?  Surely, we can all rejoice when another finally sees the light at the end of the tunnel, no?  Or, would you rather he not see the light ever?
